Product Description

We're pleased to introduce a new controller from Hori, the officially SONY licensed Mini Wired Gamepad for PlayStation 4, designed with younger gamers in mind. This controller is 40% smaller than the DualShock 4 and has a simple form factor with a flat design that makes it easy to fit into smaller hands. The Mini Wired Gamepad provides the essential functions to play most PS4 games while still providing a great gaming experience - that includes the right and left sticks, R1/L1/R2/L2 buttons, directional buttons, and action buttons. Touch pad inputs can be simulated via the left or right sticks. The wired controller includes a 3 metre cable, making for an easy plug-and-play experience. While this controller does not include some features of DualShock 4, including a touch pad, light bar, stereo headset jack, speaker, vibration, or motion sensing, it comes at a great value and helps open gaming to the whole family. Find out more about the gamepad here.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
3.0 out of 5 stars It works but
Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2022
I bought this for my toddler to play a paw patrol game on my PS4. The regular controller is way too big. This one is better but the sticks are really far from the sides of the controller, meaning they are still hard to reach without holding the controller weird. They are actually further from the sides of the controller than the regular DualShock controller, despite the controller itself being a smaller size. This kind of defeats the purpose. It doesnt matter if the sticks are close together. It matters that you can reach the sticks with your thumbs when holding the controller. I posted a pic of a side by side comparison.Its just not that much of an improvement. I also thought this was overpriced for what you get.

Rob Chasmer
5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for use with Drive Hub and steering wheels on PS5/PS4
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on March 5, 2022
Color: Black VersionVerified Purchase
For 20 you can't go wrong, a mini PlayStation controller in a similar style to the old SNES controller.

I got this as a companion controller to go with the Collective Minds Drive Hub product. That is a gadget that lets you use older/newer steering wheels on consoles that it was not designed for. E.g. I'm using a top end (but old) PC steering wheel (Logitech G25 with force feedback), metal pedals and gear stick combo on my PS4 and PS5. For it to work you plugin an official controller, just like the HORI.
The HORI is great as it's cabled with no batteries to worry about. It also means I can use the HORI pad as an alternative to access game menus to help my kids play.

P.S. All setup and working in GT (Gran Turismo 7)
